  "texts": [
    "The queries used are the same range queries as point queries but followed with an extra spatial predicate Q covers R, ensuring the candidate box R is fully covered by query box Q.Figure 11j-l presents the range query processing results.",
    "For learned indexes, querying box geometries takes 1.73× ∼ 2.19× longer time when compared to querying the corresponding point datasets.",
    "Additionally, indexes that perform well on point datasets, like Flood and IFI, also achieves better performance on box geometries.",
    "For example, Flood is 1.81× faster than STR and 1.79× faster than R*Tree.",
    "The core reason is that, in our implementation, querying over box geometries will be decomposed and transformed into several point range queries."
  ],
